    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1997) - SECTION 3.5: CIRCUIT FUNCTION AND DIAGNOSTICS - APS/IVS PEDAL
        POSITION SENSOR/IDLE VALIDATION SWITCH - FAULT DETECTION/MANAGEMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FAULT DETECTION/MANAGEMENT</title>
        <para>Any detected malfunction of the APS or IVS sensor circuit will illuminate the WARN ENGINE lamp.</para>
        <para>An APS signal that is detected out of range high or low by the ECM will cause the engine to ignore the APS
            signal and will only allow the engine to operate at low idle.
        </para>
        <para>If a disagreement in the state of IVS and APS is detected by the ECM and the ECM determines that it is an
            IVS fault, the ECM will only allow a maximum of 50% APS to be commanded.
        </para>
        <para>If a disagreement in the state of IVS and APS is detected by the ECM and the ECM can not discern if it is
            an APS or IVS fault or if it is an APS fault, the engine will be allowed to operate at low idle only.
        </para>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef1251802">3.9</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            and
            <emph type="bold">Table
                <hotlnk xrefid="et1251801">3.6</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the circuit diagram and table of the APS/IVS switch.
        </para>
